WEBVTT

00:00:01.500 --> 00:00:03.450
Is this...?

00:00:03.450 --> 00:00:04.660
A time machine.

00:00:04.660 --> 00:00:07.950
I'm from the year 2036.

00:00:07.950 --> 00:00:10.080
Suzuha...

00:00:10.080 --> 00:00:13.080
I'm the time traveler...

00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:14.870
...John Titor.

00:00:30.290 --> 00:00:35.500
For you, billions and billions of heartbeats

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:42.160
are nothing at all; just the blink of an eye

00:00:42.160 --> 00:00:47.370
Although I'm trapped by
the past and lament the future

00:00:47.370 --> 00:00:53.290
inevitability won't allow for
even a speck of a miscalculation

00:00:53.290 --> 00:00:59.410
Our dreams and futures that
form and expand into "infinity"

00:00:59.410 --> 00:01:05.290
allow us the right to be vain,

00:01:05.290 --> 00:01:11.500
while the two hands
point out what is "finite"

00:01:11.500 --> 00:01:16.080
All of which leads to a cruel
contract and choice to make

00:01:16.080 --> 00:01:18.330
Hacking to the Gate

00:01:18.330 --> 00:01:25.250
So, now, with each passing
second, I'll cross world lines

00:01:25.250 --> 00:01:30.160
to protect that smile on your face

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:37.160
Then, once again, into a
time loop without sadness

00:01:37.160 --> 00:01:43.830
I will be swallowed up as a lone observer

00:01:52.410 --> 00:01:58.450
In the year 2036, SERN ruled the world.

00:01:58.450 --> 00:02:01.500
They had complete control
of everything; it was a dystopia.

00:02:02.450 --> 00:02:06.660
The people, stripped of their freedom,
lived as if they were already dead.

00:02:06.660 --> 00:02:09.580
And anyone who stood up
in opposition was slaughtered.

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:22.120
I was a member of the resistance
that fought to free humanity from SERN.

00:02:43.200 --> 00:02:48.160
I boarded a time machine my dad left me...

00:02:48.160 --> 00:02:52.750
...to change this dying world.

00:03:15.830 --> 00:03:19.450
And to alter the future.

00:03:19.450 --> 00:03:22.250
Then all those posts on @channel were...?!

00:03:22.250 --> 00:03:24.540
Yeah. Most of them are true.

00:03:24.540 --> 00:03:29.290
But SERN's a research
organization, not a governing body.

00:03:29.290 --> 00:03:33.160
I pointed that out to
John Titor many times online!

00:03:33.160 --> 00:03:36.160
Hold on, does that mean
you're the one who posted

00:03:36.160 --> 00:03:39.120
under the name
"Chestnut Rice and Kamehame-ha"?!

00:03:39.120 --> 00:03:44.750
The person playing Titor has revealed
herself, so it's only fair that I do too.

00:03:44.750 --> 00:03:47.040
Then I'll follow suit.

00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:48.790
I posted under the
pseudonym "Hououin Kyouma"--

00:03:48.790 --> 00:03:50.950
We know.

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:56.750
SERN succeeded in developing a time machine.

00:03:56.750 --> 00:04:01.750
Being the only ones capable of
meddling with the 4th dimension of time,

00:04:01.750 --> 00:04:04.330
they were able to reshape the world order.

00:04:04.330 --> 00:04:10.120
And Makise Kurisu contributed the
most in developing SERN's time machine.

00:04:10.120 --> 00:04:12.910
She was revered as the
mother of time machines.

00:04:12.910 --> 00:04:16.330
Me, help SERN?! That's nonsense!

00:04:16.330 --> 00:04:19.790
Why would I help creeps
who use people as guinea pigs?!

00:04:19.790 --> 00:04:22.910
Well, you did, in the future.

00:04:22.910 --> 00:04:26.410
Is that why you were always
antagonistic toward me?

00:04:32.160 --> 00:04:34.040
What about my future self, then?

00:04:34.040 --> 00:04:36.950
Okabe Rintaro was a famous terrorist.

00:04:36.950 --> 00:04:37.870
A terrorist?!

00:04:37.870 --> 00:04:41.160
An anti-SERN terrorist.

00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:43.910
And...

00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:48.870
In 2036, you're both dead.

00:04:52.790 --> 00:04:55.290
-Well, I got to go.
-Wait!

00:04:55.290 --> 00:04:58.700
You're just gonna say that
and then return to the future?!

00:04:58.700 --> 00:05:02.580
No, I'm going to the past,
to change the future.

00:05:02.580 --> 00:05:05.200
Back to the year 1975.

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:07.000
1975?

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:10.040
SERN succeeded in
developing a time machine

00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:14.450
because of the one built in Akihabara in 2010.

00:05:14.450 --> 00:05:17.410
-You mean the Phone Microwave?
-Yeah.

00:05:17.410 --> 00:05:20.410
SERN used a global monitoring system

00:05:20.410 --> 00:05:25.040
to gather any and all information
regarding time machines.

00:05:25.040 --> 00:05:27.540
And, Okabe Rintaro,

00:05:27.540 --> 00:05:31.660
I think the first D-mail
you sent set off their system.

00:05:31.660 --> 00:05:33.700
The one I sent in front
of the Radio Building...?

00:05:33.700 --> 00:05:40.700
Yes. So if we can just delete
that e-mail from SERN's database...

00:05:40.700 --> 00:05:44.000
...the future will change.

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:46.000
We'll move to a beta world line

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:50.080
where SERN never
completed its time machine!

00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:53.830
Will that save Mayuri too?!

00:05:53.830 --> 00:05:54.910
Probably.

00:05:54.910 --> 00:05:57.790
Then let's hack SERN's
database right away and--!

00:05:57.790 --> 00:06:01.040
We need an IBN 5100 for that.

00:06:01.040 --> 00:06:02.870
Oh! So that's why--!

00:06:02.870 --> 00:06:08.580
My mission is to go to 1975,
obtain an IBN 5100,

00:06:08.580 --> 00:06:11.830
and get it into Okabe Rintaro's hands.

00:06:11.830 --> 00:06:16.450
But I've wasted too much time in
this time period looking for my dad.

00:06:16.450 --> 00:06:18.750
I should've gone sooner.

00:06:20.870 --> 00:06:22.450
Is everything okay?!

00:06:24.790 --> 00:06:26.830
Oh, no!

00:06:26.830 --> 00:06:28.870
It's broken...

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.080
-Not good!
-What now?!

00:06:34.080 --> 00:06:38.700
I'll figure something out! You two
hide and get away when you can!

00:06:38.700 --> 00:06:41.580
Someone in here?

00:06:41.580 --> 00:06:43.370
-Who are you?!
-Stay back!

00:06:43.370 --> 00:06:47.120
I'm currently on an assignment
to thwart an Organization plot!

00:06:47.120 --> 00:06:50.410
This is a Level 17 top-secret mission!

00:06:50.410 --> 00:06:52.750
Now leave at once!

00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:53.830
Catch me if you can!

00:06:53.830 --> 00:06:56.160
-Hey!
-Get back here!

00:06:58.370 --> 00:06:59.910
Let's make a run for it!

00:07:04.500 --> 00:07:06.450
Hurry!

00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:08.250
I don't know what happened in the future,

00:07:08.250 --> 00:07:11.500
but right now we're fellow lab members!

00:07:27.330 --> 00:07:28.660
Okabe!

00:07:28.660 --> 00:07:29.950
You made it out?!

00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:31.620
Let's scram!

00:07:38.700 --> 00:07:42.080
Now what do we do?
We can't go back there again...

00:07:42.540 --> 00:07:47.040
-So the time machine broke?
-After it crashed into the roof?

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:49.750
It didn't "crash."

00:07:49.750 --> 00:07:54.330
I miscalculated the coordinates,
and that's just where it materialized.

00:07:54.330 --> 00:07:56.830
But it wasn't broken when I arrived.

00:07:56.830 --> 00:07:57.870
Then when...?!

00:07:57.870 --> 00:08:02.370
The only possibility I can think of
is that thunderstorm the other day.

00:08:04.160 --> 00:08:09.290
It was either the
lightning or all that rainwater...

00:08:09.290 --> 00:08:11.790
It's my fault.

00:08:11.790 --> 00:08:15.120
It's because I stopped you that night...

00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:16.910
But I can use the time leap machine!

00:08:16.910 --> 00:08:21.290
It can only go back 48 hours at most, though.

00:08:21.290 --> 00:08:23.160
That makes it out of reach...

00:08:23.160 --> 00:08:24.950
Oh, Okarin!

00:08:24.950 --> 00:08:27.580
And Kurisu-chan and Suzu-san!

00:08:27.580 --> 00:08:29.910
I thought you guys went home?!

00:08:29.910 --> 00:08:33.120
Mayushii said we should
celebrate its completion after all.

00:08:33.120 --> 00:08:35.830
So Daru-kun and I picked up some things!

00:08:35.830 --> 00:08:38.080
I told you to leave for today!

00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:39.540
I'm sorry, Mayuri.

00:08:39.540 --> 00:08:43.330
We have important things to discuss now.

00:08:43.330 --> 00:08:44.500
Okarin?

00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:47.330
Just go home for today.

00:08:47.330 --> 00:08:51.620
We'll still celebrate, just some other time.

00:08:51.620 --> 00:08:53.290
Okay.

00:08:53.290 --> 00:08:55.450
But don't do anything dangerous, okay?

00:08:55.450 --> 00:08:57.620
Mayushii worries about you.

00:08:57.620 --> 00:09:01.370
We'll be okay. I promise.

00:09:04.660 --> 00:09:06.790
See you tomorrow!

00:09:06.790 --> 00:09:08.410
Yeah.

00:09:13.750 --> 00:09:16.910
-I hear they stopped the trains.
-You serious?

00:09:25.330 --> 00:09:28.500
Our only choice is to repair the time machine.

00:09:34.950 --> 00:09:37.330
First, you'll jump to five hours ago--

00:09:37.330 --> 00:09:41.160
when the time leap machine
is finished, in other words.

00:09:41.160 --> 00:09:46.080
Then you'll jump another
48 hours back, to 2:00 pm on the 11th.

00:09:46.080 --> 00:09:50.330
I guess that's all the
time we have to work with.

00:09:50.330 --> 00:09:54.830
I'll do whatever it takes to fix the
time machine within those two days.

00:09:54.830 --> 00:09:58.700
If it doesn't work out, then
I'll just keep redoing those two days!

00:10:01.330 --> 00:10:04.910
This isn't about saving the world.

00:10:04.910 --> 00:10:07.950
It's about saving Mayuri!

00:10:20.700 --> 00:10:22.200
Okabe?

00:10:22.200 --> 00:10:23.200
What's the matter?

00:10:23.200 --> 00:10:25.950
Get all the lab members here right away.

00:10:25.950 --> 00:10:28.200
I have something to tell you.

00:10:32.450 --> 00:10:35.700
Sweet! Future people FTW!

00:10:35.700 --> 00:10:37.330
Can you fix it?

00:10:37.330 --> 00:10:39.870
You can't fix it yourself, Miss Amane?

00:10:39.870 --> 00:10:42.120
I have no idea how it works.

00:10:42.120 --> 00:10:44.330
My dad's the one who made it.

00:10:44.330 --> 00:10:48.200
We can't possibly fix a time
machine from 2036 with current tech--

00:10:48.200 --> 00:10:50.200
We won't know unless we try!

00:10:50.200 --> 00:10:52.870
Just figure something
out within two days, Daru!

00:10:52.870 --> 00:10:56.080
-You're our only hope!
-Why two days?

00:10:57.450 --> 00:10:58.830
Well, uhh...

00:10:58.830 --> 00:11:00.500
Just do it in two days!

00:11:00.500 --> 00:11:03.290
If you can fix it in two days,
I'll do whatever you ask!

00:11:03.290 --> 00:11:04.290
Deal!

00:11:04.290 --> 00:11:06.660
I want to go on an
all-day date with Faris-tan!

00:11:06.660 --> 00:11:08.290
All right. I'll make it happen somehow.

00:11:08.290 --> 00:11:11.040
-No, there's no way.
-There's nothing I can't do!

00:11:11.040 --> 00:11:12.660
Trust me!

00:11:15.120 --> 00:11:16.910
Serious? You swear?

00:11:16.910 --> 00:11:19.750
I promise! Just get it done!

00:11:21.750 --> 00:11:23.370
Very well!

00:11:25.370 --> 00:11:27.410
One more thing?

00:11:27.410 --> 00:11:31.080
If I fix it, bring us back the IBN 5100

00:11:31.080 --> 00:11:34.750
and an animation cel from the
legendary 1975 magical series,

00:11:34.750 --> 00:11:36.750
"Radical Girl Omit-chan"!

00:11:36.750 --> 00:11:38.500
Have some self-respect!

00:11:38.500 --> 00:11:40.080
Shall I help too?

00:11:40.080 --> 00:11:45.910
No, you have the important task
of completing the time leap machine.

00:11:45.910 --> 00:11:48.370
-You should probably get back to the--
-Hey, everyone!

00:11:48.370 --> 00:11:50.700
Is it me, or are you forgetting something?

00:11:50.700 --> 00:11:52.750
What about finding Suzu-san's dad?

00:11:52.750 --> 00:11:55.330
-My dad doesn't matter anymore--
-Don't say that!

00:11:55.330 --> 00:11:59.580
I know you used the machine
because you have a mission and stuff,

00:11:59.580 --> 00:12:02.750
but you also did it to see your dad, right?

00:12:02.750 --> 00:12:06.370
So Mayushii wants you two to meet!

00:12:07.790 --> 00:12:10.370
Your father's name was Barrel Titor, right?

00:12:10.370 --> 00:12:13.250
That's his code name.
I don't know his real one.

00:12:13.250 --> 00:12:16.120
-What about "Amane"?
-I got it from my mom.

00:12:16.120 --> 00:12:21.200
My only clue is this one memento:
a badge my dad used to have.

00:12:24.290 --> 00:12:28.540
You're dad's in Akihabara in 2010, right?

00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:32.660
In that case, Mayushii will
begin investigating at once!

00:12:34.200 --> 00:12:37.500
Shiina Mayuri is a nice girl, huh?

00:12:50.540 --> 00:12:51.790
Think you can fix it?

00:12:51.790 --> 00:12:55.830
I'm not 100% sure yet, but
after giving it a quick look-over

00:12:55.830 --> 00:13:00.080
I noticed it's actually kinda
like the Phone Microwave...

00:13:00.080 --> 00:13:03.000
Then you might be able to fix it?!

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:04.660
Yeah.

00:13:05.290 --> 00:13:09.410
You know, I wonder if your
dad's someone close to us.

00:13:09.410 --> 00:13:14.290
After all, you knew we
were in Akiba in 2010...

00:13:14.290 --> 00:13:17.870
Probably. He didn't tell me himself, so...

00:13:17.870 --> 00:13:24.790
I've never actually met my dad;
it was all written in his will.

00:13:24.790 --> 00:13:29.410
He was doing his own time
machine research separate from SERN,

00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:31.790
to try to change the future.

00:13:31.790 --> 00:13:35.450
And now I'm here to carry out his wish.

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:40.830
I'm seriously sorry.

00:13:40.830 --> 00:13:44.330
But I'm sure everything will
work out after I fix the time machine!

00:13:44.330 --> 00:13:49.830
I'll keep looking for your dad
until you come back from 1975!

00:13:49.830 --> 00:13:54.660
So keep it a secret from Okarin
and snag me a legendary "Radical--"

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.700
This is such tedious work.

00:14:03.700 --> 00:14:06.160
For a so-called Future Gadget Laboratory,

00:14:06.160 --> 00:14:08.620
you'd think we'd have a
more futuristic way to do this.

00:14:08.620 --> 00:14:11.580
If only it were that convenient.

00:14:19.080 --> 00:14:24.790
Future Gadget #2,
Alternative Edition, Version 2.67.

00:14:24.790 --> 00:14:27.040
Known as the "Bamboo-copter Camera."

00:14:27.040 --> 00:14:30.500
It has a CCD camera installed in the bottom.

00:14:30.500 --> 00:14:32.540
That's actually a decent idea!

00:14:32.540 --> 00:14:34.580
Couldn't we conduct an aerial search--

00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:38.830
The camera spins with it, so the
footage it takes spins rapidly too.

00:14:38.830 --> 00:14:42.250
That hasn't been fixed, even by Version 2.67?

00:14:42.250 --> 00:14:43.950
That's the prototype.

00:14:43.950 --> 00:14:49.830
Daru gave it the name and version
number for fun. There's no meaning to it.

00:14:51.870 --> 00:14:54.910
-Where's Daru?
-Still there, working on it.

00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:00.500
The Divergence Meter...

00:15:12.790 --> 00:15:19.120
I thought you should have this.
You created it, after all.

00:15:19.120 --> 00:15:23.700
The future will change
if this number passes 1%.

00:15:23.700 --> 00:15:26.750
And since you're the only one
with the Reading Steiner ability,

00:15:26.750 --> 00:15:29.000
only you can perceive
how the number changes.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:33.000
Did my future self give that
to you just before he died?

00:15:33.000 --> 00:15:37.000
No. I've never met him.

00:15:37.000 --> 00:15:42.410
You were a founder of the
resistance group I'm a member of.

00:15:42.410 --> 00:15:45.500
A founder of a resistance group...

00:15:45.500 --> 00:15:47.620
That's pathetic.

00:15:47.620 --> 00:15:49.370
Not only do I let Mayuri die,

00:15:49.370 --> 00:15:53.200
I go on to live a carefree life
and do something so delusional...?!

00:15:53.200 --> 00:15:55.000
It's not pathetic!

00:15:55.000 --> 00:16:00.410
Liberating the world is a
brave and admirable ambition!

00:16:32.540 --> 00:16:33.950
Uhh...

00:16:33.950 --> 00:16:35.580
Hey, mister!

00:16:37.290 --> 00:16:39.200
I am mad scientist!

00:16:39.200 --> 00:16:40.950
So cool!

00:16:40.950 --> 00:16:42.580
Sunovabitch.

00:16:43.830 --> 00:16:46.620
Yes, can I help you?

00:16:46.620 --> 00:16:48.370
Oh, you know Japanese...

00:16:48.370 --> 00:16:50.500
I got a question for you.

00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:52.500
Do you recognize this?

00:16:52.500 --> 00:16:56.250
I wanna know where
it's from. Can you find out?

00:16:56.250 --> 00:16:58.950
Oh, remembering is...

00:16:58.950 --> 00:17:01.910
Sorry. No can help.

00:17:01.910 --> 00:17:05.410
Actually, I'm not so
sure about his Japanese...

00:17:06.120 --> 00:17:09.910
If you remember anything, contact me here.

00:17:15.450 --> 00:17:20.910
Maybe it doesn't exist yet because
it's made sometime in the near future?

00:17:20.910 --> 00:17:25.500
I guess maybe I'm just
not destined to meet my dad.

00:17:25.500 --> 00:17:28.040
-Let's call it quits.
-You're just gonna give up?!

00:17:28.040 --> 00:17:30.540
We still have a day left, you know!

00:17:30.540 --> 00:17:32.290
-Why are you upset--
-More than anything...

00:17:32.290 --> 00:17:34.660
...I want to make saving Mayuri my main focus!

00:17:34.660 --> 00:17:37.450
Even so, you're a fellow
lab member and a friend!

00:17:37.450 --> 00:17:39.910
You're a friend in need, so I want to help!

00:17:39.910 --> 00:17:43.450
But you can't just give
up at the drop of a hat!

00:17:43.450 --> 00:17:46.120
D-Don't yell at me.

00:17:50.290 --> 00:17:52.580
Sorry.

00:17:52.580 --> 00:17:55.870
-Please, I need your help! Please!
-What is she...?

00:17:55.870 --> 00:17:58.790
There was a kidnapping yesterday!

00:17:58.790 --> 00:18:01.700
I'm looking for the kidnapper!
He was wearing this badge!

00:18:01.700 --> 00:18:05.500
I would appreciate your help!

00:18:05.500 --> 00:18:07.450
Oh! Okarin!

00:18:07.450 --> 00:18:09.080
Look! Look!

00:18:09.580 --> 00:18:10.580
"Hit the kidnapper with the Justice Hammer! The kidnapper
is wearing this badge! He could be your neighbor!"

00:18:13.450 --> 00:18:15.500
Mayuri...

00:18:15.500 --> 00:18:17.290
Good plan, huh?

00:18:17.290 --> 00:18:19.750
It was Mayushii's idea!

00:18:19.750 --> 00:18:23.870
I thought it might
make everyone go, "Oh!"

00:18:23.870 --> 00:18:26.950
The plan's name is "Mayushii
Pamphlets Her Way to Victory!"

00:18:26.950 --> 00:18:30.040
Don't you think saying there was
a kidnapping is going a little far...?

00:18:30.040 --> 00:18:33.500
What happens when
the police take notice of--?

00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:35.580
-Oh, no! Let's get outta here!
-Huh? What for?

00:18:35.580 --> 00:18:36.870
You, there!

00:18:36.870 --> 00:18:38.290
Hey, wait!

00:18:43.790 --> 00:18:45.000
I'm sorry...

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:50.870
From now on, run all plans--
and plan names--by me first...

00:18:56.000 --> 00:18:57.540
What are you doing?

00:18:58.410 --> 00:19:00.200
Oh, it's just you, Christina.

00:19:00.200 --> 00:19:03.540
This is good timing. I just
found out something terrible.

00:19:03.540 --> 00:19:05.370
What?

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:10.950
When I went to buy lunch,
I overheard the shop clerks talking.

00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:14.500
I think your father might
be a kidnapper, Amane-san...

00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:24.000
Wh-What? What's going on?

00:19:29.790 --> 00:19:31.450
How's it going?

00:19:31.450 --> 00:19:33.700
For you.

00:19:33.700 --> 00:19:39.540
WTF, dude. This work clearly
calls for ice-cold, no-calorie cola.

00:19:39.540 --> 00:19:41.620
Well? Do you think you can repair it?

00:19:41.620 --> 00:19:43.290
Should have it done by tomorrow.

00:19:43.290 --> 00:19:45.870
Wow! I know it's a rush job, but wow!

00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:48.040
Daru's got serious skills, all right.

00:19:48.040 --> 00:19:51.250
He seems so unhealthy and
drab on the outside, though.

00:19:51.250 --> 00:19:53.040
Don't judge a book by its cover.

00:19:53.040 --> 00:19:55.160
Right! I've changed my opinion of him!

00:19:55.160 --> 00:19:57.500
Then you can help me too, Miss Amane.

00:19:57.500 --> 00:20:00.500
And, inside the cramped time machine,
the sweltering heat will be so much

00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:03.620
that we'll forget our
embarrassment and strip our clothes...

00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.330
Have some self-respect, pervert!

00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:07.620
Daru-kun and Suzu-san
sure make a good match!

00:20:07.620 --> 00:20:10.000
Huh?! A good match?!

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:11.250
In what way?!

00:20:11.250 --> 00:20:15.160
I can't quite put my
finger on it, but they just do.

00:20:15.160 --> 00:20:17.040
-What's going on?
-Oh, nothing.

00:20:17.040 --> 00:20:19.290
Mayuri's just being weird.

00:20:19.290 --> 00:20:21.290
Still, I'll be really worried about you

00:20:21.290 --> 00:20:24.000
after the time machine
is fixed and you leave in it!

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:27.370
I'd go with you, if only
it could carry two people.

00:20:27.370 --> 00:20:29.200
What help would you be?

00:20:29.200 --> 00:20:30.790
Isn't it obvious?!

00:20:30.790 --> 00:20:34.700
I'd hold Suzu-san's hand real
tight and support her by saying,

00:20:34.700 --> 00:20:39.120
"Don't worry! You'll be fine!
Mayushii's here for you!"

00:20:45.330 --> 00:20:48.290
Listen, I feel like I might never
get another chance to say this,

00:20:48.290 --> 00:20:50.450
so I'll just say it now...

00:20:50.450 --> 00:20:53.120
Oh? That sounds a little over-the-top.

00:20:53.120 --> 00:20:57.910
I'm really grateful to you all.

00:20:57.910 --> 00:21:02.290
When I first came to this
time period, I didn't know anyone,

00:21:02.290 --> 00:21:05.370
and even though this
era's so much more peaceful,

00:21:05.370 --> 00:21:09.910
I found it really frightening.

00:21:09.910 --> 00:21:13.950
But now I have so many friends.

00:21:13.950 --> 00:21:15.830
I really had a lot of fun,

00:21:15.830 --> 00:21:21.120
coming to this era
and spending time with you.

00:21:21.120 --> 00:21:24.870
Even if it was for a short time, I'm
glad to have been a fellow lab member.

00:21:24.870 --> 00:21:29.910
I'm glad... I could be with you guys.

00:21:29.910 --> 00:21:31.910
Suzuha...

00:21:31.910 --> 00:21:33.620
Okabe Rintaro!

00:21:33.620 --> 00:21:35.410
Promise you'll change the future, okay?

00:21:35.410 --> 00:21:38.790
Make it a free world, like it is now!

00:21:38.790 --> 00:21:40.620
Suzuha...

00:21:43.080 --> 00:21:44.910
Yes?

00:21:44.910 --> 00:21:48.200
Hello? Mad scientist so cool?

00:21:48.200 --> 00:21:49.950
The street vendor from this afternoon?

00:21:49.950 --> 00:21:51.950
I just remembered.

00:21:51.950 --> 00:21:54.290
Yesterday night. A man with that badge.

00:21:54.290 --> 00:21:56.660
You found her father?!

00:21:56.660 --> 00:21:58.830
Hang on! I'll be right there!

00:22:20.830 --> 00:22:23.790
With my vision restricted,

00:22:23.790 --> 00:22:29.700
there's no escape

00:22:29.700 --> 00:22:34.040
from the merciless control

00:22:34.040 --> 00:22:37.450
of the twelve

00:22:37.450 --> 00:22:41.370
Wishing for

00:22:41.370 --> 00:22:46.330
a tomorrow of repose,

00:22:46.330 --> 00:22:50.450
I embark for the horizon

00:22:50.450 --> 00:22:54.950
of the sacred phenomenon in my hand

00:22:54.950 --> 00:22:59.120
Trapped by the covenant

00:22:59.120 --> 00:23:03.580
and shown the outline of false evidence

00:23:03.580 --> 00:23:07.750
the heaven and earth

00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:12.790
of life lets time blindly flow by

00:23:12.790 --> 00:23:17.950
Flutter, butterfly, oh, miraculous butterfly!

00:23:17.950 --> 00:23:21.620
I give myself to you

00:23:21.620 --> 00:23:26.000
Oh, butterfly of tears, dazzling butterfly!

00:23:26.000 --> 00:23:28.830
It's all...

00:23:28.830 --> 00:23:33.830
...about to be rewritten now

